The paper proposes a game-theoretic approach for identifying malicious nodes in VANETs, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also deals with the problem of misbehavior detection in VANETs, which is a subfield of networked systems (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of uncertainty on the behavior of nodes, which is related to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The proposed approach also involves designing incentives to promote cooperation, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
